 The body of a 6-year-old has been recovered following floods in Coffee Bay in the Eastern Cape. Some major roads have also been washed out leaving residents trapped in surrounding villages. For more, eNCA speaks to Sipelele Ndungane, a business owner in the area. #DStv403Show less JOHANNESBURG - The body of a six-year-old girl who was swept away during floods in Coffee Bay in the Eastern Cape has been recovered. At least five other people are still missing. READ: SA Weather | 2 die in Eastern Cape floods Residents of the Wild Coast town are some of the most affected by the floods that wreaked havoc across large parts of the province. Major roads in the area have also been washed away leaving residents trapped in surrounding villages.